 M_{t+h} = E\left( \int^{t+h}_{0}X_{s}ds |G_{t+h}\right) -\int^{t+h}_{0} E(X_{s}|G_{s})ds\\ M_t = E\left( \int^{t}_{0}X_{s}ds| G_{t+h} G_{t}\right)-\int^{t}_{0} E(X_{s}|G_{s})ds  \\ M_{t+h} - M_t = E\left( \int^{t+h}_{0}X_{s}ds | G_{t+h}\right) -\int^{t+h}_{t} E(X_{s}|G_{s})ds - E\left(  \int^{t}_{0}X_{s}ds | G_{t}\right)\\ E(M_{t+h} - M_t|G_t)= E\left( \int^{t+h}_{0}X_{s}ds | G_{t}\right) -\int^{t+h}_{t} E(X_{s}|G_{t})ds - E\left(  \int^{t}_{0}X_{s}ds | G_{t}\right) =0 
